        <!-- ========================= service-section start ========================= -->
        <section id="service" class="service-section pt-120 pb-120">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-xl-10 col-lg-10 mx-auto">
                        <div class="section-title text-center mb-55">
                            <h2 class="mb-20 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".2s">Strategy: Fusion</h2>
                            <p class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".4s">Fusion is a signal-driven multi-asset Portfolio Management Strategy (PMS) designed to deliver stable, risk-managed compounding across market cycles. Below we outline the strategy overview, key features, returns, and frequently asked questions.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- 4.1 Fusion – Overview -->
                <div class="row align-items-center mb-40">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 wow fadeInLeft" data-wow-delay=".2s">
                        <div class="fusion-img text-center">
                            <img src="assets/img/feature-2.svg" alt="Fusion overview" style="max-width:360px">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-6 wow fadeInRight" data-wow-delay=".4s">
                        <h3 class="mb-15">4.1 Fusion – Overview</h3>
                        <p><strong>What Fusion is</strong> — A signal-driven multi-asset PMS that blends valuation, regime detection and momentum signals to allocate across equities, quality factors, and defensive assets.</p>
                        <p><strong>Objective</strong> — Stable compounding with risk-managed exposure: target attractive long-term growth while limiting large drawdowns through active risk management.</p>
                        <p><strong>Philosophy</strong> — Discipline, diversification and evidence-based rules. Fusion favors systematic, transparent rules over discretionary bets and emphasizes structural robustness.</p>
                        <p><strong>Key components</strong> — Valuation bands to gauge cheap/expensive markets; regime detection to identify bull/bear/backdrop; asset rotation across asset classes; tactical overlays for drawdown protection.</p>
                        <p><strong>Suitable investor profile</strong> — Investors seeking long-term capital growth with an emphasis on downside protection, a multi-year investment horizon, and a tolerance for moderate short-term volatility.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- 4.2 Fusion – Features -->
                <div class="row align-items-center mb-40">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 order-lg-2 wow fadeInRight" data-wow-delay=".2s">
                        <div class="fusion-img text-center">
                            <img src="assets/img/feature-3.svg" alt="Fusion features" style="max-width:360px">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-6 order-lg-1 wow fadeInLeft" data-wow-delay=".4s">
                        <h3 class="mb-15">4.2 Fusion – Features</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Rule-based decision engine</strong> — Deterministic rules convert market signals into portfolio decisions, ensuring repeatability and auditability.</li>
                            <li><strong>Regime-aware risk model</strong> — Adjusts allocations and risk budgets based on detected market regimes to reduce exposure in adverse environments.</li>
                            <li><strong>Dynamic asset allocation</strong> — Rotates capital across Quality, Momentum, and defensive assets (Gold/Debt) depending on signal strength.</li>
                            <li><strong>Drawdown protection overlays</strong> — Tactical overlays (options, hedges or cash buffers) are applied when downside risk is elevated.</li>
                            <li><strong>Low churn + disciplined execution</strong> — Minimizes transaction costs by only trading when signals cross thresholds; execution follows strict slippage controls.</li>
                            <li><strong>Investment universe</strong> — A diversified universe including large-cap equities, factor buckets (e.g., quality/momentum), sovereign bonds, and gold.</li>
                            <li><strong>Transparent and auditable process</strong> — All rules and signals are versioned, backtests and trade logs are maintained for auditability.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- 4.3 Fusion – Returns -->
                <div class="row align-items-center mb-40">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 wow fadeInLeft" data-wow-delay=".2s">
                        <div class="fusion-img text-center">
                            <img src="assets/img/about-img.svg" alt="Fusion returns" style="max-width:360px">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-6 wow fadeInRight" data-wow-delay=".4s">
                        <h3 class="mb-15">4.3 Fusion – Returns</h3>
                        <p>Latest performance snapshot (placeholder). Below is a sample annual/calendar table and a benchmark comparison. Replace with live data to reflect accurate performance.</p>
                        <div class="table-responsive mb-30">
                            <table class="table table-striped">
                                <thead>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th>Year</th>
                                        <th>Fusion Return</th>
                                        <th>Benchmark Return</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
